# Ignore everything, then allow back only what the Dockerfile COPYs.
# Without this, `fly deploy` uploads the whole working tree — target/
# (gigabytes of Rust artifacts), the vendored lib/ submodules, and .git —
# to Fly's remote builder, blowing the context-upload deadline
# ("context deadline exceeded"). The submodules are cloned fresh inside
# the build (see Dockerfile), so none of that local state is needed.
*
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!config.toml
!.gitmodules
!src
!artifacts
